2 SENATE BILL 852
1 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
2 Section 11–1002
3 Annotated Code of Maryland
4 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
5 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
6 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
7 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
8 11–102.
9 This title applies only in Anne Arundel County.
10 11–1002.
11 (a) There is a barbershop and beauty salon beer [and], wine, AND LIQUOR
12 license.
13 (b) The Board may issue the license to a holder of:
14 (1) a barbershop permit issued under § 4–501 of the Business Occupations
15 and Professions Article; or
16 (2) a beauty salon permit issued under § 5–501 of the Business Occupations
17 and Professions Article.
18 (c) The license authorizes the license holder to provide TO A CUSTOMER DURING
19 ANY ONE VISIT not more than 12 ounces of beer [or], 5 ounces of wine by the glass, OR 1.7
20 OUNCES OF LIQUOR for on–premises consumption by a THE barbershop or beauty salon
21 customer:
22 (1) when the customer is being provided:
23 (i) a barbering service under Title 4 of the Business Occupations
24 and Professions Article; or
25 (ii) a cosmetology service under Title 5 of the Business Occupations
26 and Professions Article; or
27 (2) while the customer is attending a fund–raising event at the barbershop
28 or beauty salon.
29 (d) A license holder may serve beer [and], wine, AND LIQUOR for on–premises
30 consumption during normal business hours but not later than 9 p.m.

SENATE BILL 852 3
1 (e) A license holder need not obtain a Sunday license under § 11–2004 of this title
2 to provide beer [and], wine, AND LIQUOR on Sunday.
3 (f) The annual license fee is $100.
4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
5 1, 2026.
Approved:
